% Section 4
\smallskip
\Exer  Solve each of the following systems by Gauss-Jordan elimination
{\it if there is a solution}.

(a)
$$
\align
x_1 + 2x_2 + 3x_3 &= 4 \\
3x_1 + x_2 + 2x_3 &= -1 \\
x_1 \quad\qquad + x_3 &= 0 
\endalign
$$

(b)
$$
\align
x_1 + 2x_2 + 3x_3 &= 4 \\
2x_1 + 3x_2 + 2x_3 &= -1 \\
x_1  + x_2 - x_3 &= 10 
\endalign
$$

(c)
$$
\bm\format\r&&\quad\r\\
  1 & 1 & -2 & 3 \\
  2 & 1 & 0 & 1 \\
  1 & -1 & 1 & 0 \\
  3 & 1 & 2 & 1 \em
\bm x_1\\ x_2\\ x_3 \\ x_4 \em
=
\bm\format\r\\ 9 \\ -18 \\ -9 \\ 9 \em.
$$
\answer  (a)  $x_1 = -3/2, x_2 = 1/2, x_3 = 3/2$.\par
(b)  No solutions. \par
(c) $x_1 = -27, x_2 = 9, x_3 = 27, x_4 = 27$.  In vector form,
$$
\x = \bm -27\\ 9\\ 27\\ 27 \em.
$$
 
