    7 & 8 & 9 \em
$$

\Exer  What is the effect of mulitplying a $2\times 2$ matrix $A$
on the right by the elementary matrix
$$
\bm 1 & a \\ 0 & 1 \em?
$$
What general rule is this a special case of?
\answer The effect is to add $a$ times the first {\it column\/}
to the second {\it column}.   The general rule is that if you multiply
a matrix on the right
 by the matrix with an $a$ in the $i,j$-position ($i\not=j$)
and ones on the diagonal, the effect is to add $a$ times the
$i$th column to the $j$th column.

